It also didn't include people who got sick in nursing homes, but then died at hospitals.
“We’ve been talking about nursing homes every day for the past 30 days,” Cuomo said.
“We’ve said 157 times the most vulnerable population are seniors, the most vulnerable places are nursing homes.
Nursing homes have been known since the earliest days of the outbreak as a likely trouble spot.
Yet even with that early warning, many nursing homes remained without adequate supplies of personal protective equipment.